chief-stepping-down-after-elections-triumph%2Famp_articleshow%2F106356323.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fswiss-hard-right-chief-stepping-down-after-elections-triumph%2Famp_articleshow%2F106356323.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Memoir%20Chronicles%20How%20Israel%20Failed%20to%20Become%20the%20Promised%20Land%20for%20All%20Jews%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F15164743%2Ftaylor-brandon-Y8r0RTNrIWM-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CQu%E2%80%99est-ce%20qu%20%E2%80%98une%20nation%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhat%20is%20a%20nation%3F)%2C%E2%80%9D%20French%20scholar%20Ernest%20Renan%20had%20famously%20asked%20in%201882.%20A%20nation%20was%20not%2C%20he%20suggested%2C%20a%20racial%2C%20linguistic%2C%20religious%20or%20geographical%20construct%3B%20instead%2C%20it%20was%20%E2%80%98a%20spiritual%20principle%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20was%20forged%20through%20%E2%80%9Cforgetting%20%E2%80%A6%5Bor%5D%20historical%20error.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20a%20nation%20is%20one%20that%20has%20agreed%20to%20forget%20certain%20things%20in%20its%20past.%20Avi%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20memoir%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20Worlds%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20turns%20the%20spotlight%20back%20on%20some%20of%20the%20things%20that%20the%20Jewish%20nation%2C%20centred%20on%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20prefers%20to%20forget%20or%20suppress.%20It%20is%20a%20moving%20history%20of%20not%20just%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20pre-eminent%20historians%20and%20observers%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20also%20of%20a%20lost%20world%20in%20which%20Arabs%20and%20Jews%20had%20a%20shared%20past%20and%20a%20shared%20presence%2C%20one%20in%20which%20there%20was%20nothing%20preordained%20in%20the%20hostility%20that%20defines%20their%20current%20existence.%20In%20the%20words%20of%20the%20author%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%201947%20%E2%80%93%2049%2C%20it%20was%20not%20only%20the%20land%20of%20Palestine%20that%20was%20partitioned%2C%20but%20also%20the%20past.%20The%20common%20past%20of%20Jews%20and%20Muslims%20in%20Iraq%20was%20superseded%20by%20the%20new%20reality%20of%20the%20Arab-Israeli%20conflict.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20361px)%2085vw%2C%20361px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent-665x1024.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22361%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent-665x1024.jpeg%20665w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent-195x300.jpeg%20195w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194455%2Fcontent.jpeg%20779w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690940%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22556%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThree%20Worlds%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew.%20Oneworld%20Publications%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnsurprisingly%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20political%20book.%20Reading%20it%20today%20as%20the%20fires%20of%20conflict%20rage%20yet%20again%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20the%20enormity%20of%20what%20was%20lost%20in%20the%20way%20in%20which%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20was%20born%20and%20shaped%20by%20its%20first%20leaders%20is%20thrown%20into%20stark%20relief%20by%20the%20rising%20body%20count%20in%20the%20region.%20Then%20again%2C%20this%20is%20a%20memoir%20of%20loss.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Shlaim%20calls%20it%20a%20%E2%80%98revisionist%20tract%2C%20a%20transgressive%20document.%E2%80%99%20The%20transgression%20lies%20in%20identifying%20proudly%20as%20an%20Arab-Jew%20whose%20family%20had%20been%20integrated%20into%20the%20life%20and%20culture%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%3B%20caught%20in%20the%20cross-fire%20of%20Zionism%20and%20Arab%20nationalism%2C%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20family%20were%20compelled%20to%20move%20to%20the%20fledgling%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20move%20that%20is%20lamented%2C%20not%20lauded.%20The%20very%20hyphen%20in%20his%20identity%2C%20which%20celebrates%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20roots%20in%20Iraq%2C%20is%20anathema%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20lonely%20outpost%20of%20Jewish%20sanctuary%20in%20a%20sea%20of%20Arab%20hostility.%20The%20revisionism%20comes%20from%20questioning%20the%20founding%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20uniformly%20good%20thing%20for%20all%20Jews%2C%20because%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98monumental%20injustice%E2%80%99%20done%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20late%201940s%2C%20the%20founding%20of%20Israel%20produced%20another%20set%20of%20victims%3A%20the%20Jews%20of%20Arab%20lands%2C%20such%20as%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20who%20were%20alienated%20by%20the%20Zionist%20project%20from%20the%20land%20of%20their%20birth%2C%20from%20their%20culture%2C%20their%20languages%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20from%20their%20history.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShlaim%20was%20born%20into%20upper%20middle-class%20Iraqi-Jewish%20family%20in%201945%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20son%20of%20a%20prosperous%20businessman%2C%20whose%20family%2C%20and%20whose%20wife%E2%80%99s%20family%20traced%20their%20roots%20back%20to%20Iraq%20for%20generations.%20(Shlaimi%E2%80%99s%20maternal%20great-grandfather%20moved%20to%20India%20to%20make%20his%20fortune%2C%20working%20for%20the%20Sassoons%20in%20Bombay%2C%20before%20eventually%20moving%20back%20to%20Baghdad.)%20They%20were%2C%20quite%20simply%2C%20%E2%80%98Iraqis%20whose%20religion%20happened%20to%20be%20Jewish.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Shlaims%20were%20fully%20integrated%20into%20Iraqi%20society%2C%20speaking%20Arabic%2C%20mixing%20with%20Muslims%20and%20Jews%2C%20and%20thinking%20of%20themselves%20as%20native%20to%20that%20multicultural%20land%20%E2%80%93%20an%20Iraq%20where%20%E2%80%98the%20main%20criterion%20for%20differentiating%20between%20Jews%20and%20Arabs%20%E2%80%A6%20was%20religion%2C%20and%20only%20as%20an%20identifying%20characteristic%20and%20not%20a%20divisive%20one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20changed%20with%20the%20founding%20of%20Israel.%20Israel%20gave%20Judaism%20a%20territorial%20base.%20While%20this%20was%20a%20sanctuary%20for%20European%20Jews%20still%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20for%20the%20Jews%20of%20the%20Near%20East%2C%20the%20founding%20of%20a%20homeland%20for%20all%20Jews%20undermined%20their%20roots%20in%20Babylon%20that%20could%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20sixth%20century%20BCE.%20Jews%20had%20been%20a%20protected%2C%20yet%20well-integrated%20minority%20under%20the%20Ottoman%20Empire.%20At%20the%20start%20of%20the%20first%20world%20war%2C%20Jews%20constituted%20one%20third%20of%20Baghdad%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20a%20city%20that%20was%20often%20regarded%20as%20Jewish.%20Within%20years%20of%20the%20end%20of%20the%20second%20world%20war%2C%20Baghdad%E2%80%99s%20Jewish%20population%20was%20all%20but%20gone.%20They%20were%20victims%20of%20a%20political%20struggle%20between%20two%20competing%20%E2%80%98secular%E2%80%99%20ideologies%20of%20Arab%20nationalism%20and%20Zionism%20%E2%80%93%20one%2C%20that%20made%20them%20feel%20less%20welcome%20in%20the%20land%20of%20their%20birth%2C%20and%20the%20other%20that%20insisted%20that%20they%20could%20only%20be%20safe%20in%20the%20land%20of%20their%20religion.%20And%20thus%20the%20Shlaim%20family%20lost%20the%20land%20of%20their%20birth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20chronicle%20of%20loss%20begins%20with%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20Israel%20at%20the%20age%20of%20five.%20A%20combination%20of%20general%20attacks%20on%20Jews%20(some%20of%20which%20the%20historian%20in%20him%20has%20traced%20back%20to%20the%20Zionist%20underground%20%E2%80%93%20an%20attempt%20to%20push%20Jews%20towards%20the%20newly%20created%20Israel)%20and%20a%20specific%20sense%20of%20insecurity%20caused%20by%20criminals%20targeting%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20wealth%2C%20had%20caused%20his%20mother%20to%20conclude%20that%20Iraq%20was%20unsafe%20for%20the%20family.%20The%20move%2C%20however%2C%20extracted%20a%20heavy%20toll.%20They%20left%20behind%20their%20comfortable%20home%20and%20lifestyle%2C%20their%20language%2C%20their%20culture%2C%20their%20history%2C%20their%20past%2C%20and%20even%20their%20names.%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20mother%20and%20older%20sister%20yielded%20to%20the%20pressure%20to%20adopt%20more%20Hebrew%20names%3B%20Avi%E2%80%99s%20name%20morphed%20from%20Abi%20(for%20Abraham)%20to%20Avi%20(Avraham).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20375px)%2085vw%2C%20375px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194705%2FAvi_Shlaim.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194705%2FAvi_Shlaim.jpg%20375w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F28194705%2FAvi_Shlaim-225x300.jpg%20225w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690942%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAvi%20Shlaim.%20Photo%3A%20Mans2014%2FWikimedia%20commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20some%20of%20the%20most%20moving%20parts%20of%20this%20story%2C%20Shlaim%20explores%20what%20the%20move%20meant%20for%20his%20father%2C%20Yusef%20Shlaim%2C%20who%20arrived%20in%20Israel%20after%20his%20wife%20and%20children%2C%20having%20stayed%20behind%20to%20try%20to%20settle%20his%20affairs.%20Yusef%20was%20broken%20by%20the%20relocation.%20Until%20the%20age%20of%2050%2C%20he%20had%20been%20a%20successful%20Iraqi%20Jew%2C%20steeped%20in%20the%20ways%20and%20customs%20of%20the%20land%20of%20his%20birth.%20The%20move%20to%20Israel%20stripped%20him%20of%20it%20all.%20His%20standing%20in%20society%2C%20his%20wealth%2C%20his%20self-worth%2C%20all%20of%20it%20disappeared%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Zion%20where%20Arabic%20culture%20was%20actively%20suppressed.%20At%20its%20most%20basic%2C%20the%20move%20stripped%20him%20of%20his%20language%2C%20for%20Yusef%20was%20never%20able%20to%20communicate%20fluently%20in%20Hebrew.%20Arabic%20was%20looked%20down%20upon%2C%20and%20in%20one%20searing%20episode%2C%20Avi%20describes%20how%2C%20as%20a%20little%20boy%2C%20he%20squirmed%20in%20embarrassment%20when%20his%20father%20came%20across%20him%20playing%20with%20his%20friends%20and%20spoke%20to%20him%20in%20Arabic.%20The%20language%20of%20his%20forefathers%20had%20become%20a%20source%20of%20shame%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98promised%20land%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYusef%E2%80%99s%20story%20encapsulates%20the%20plight%20of%20so%20many%20Iraqis%20forced%20to%20leave%20their%20homes%2C%20only%20to%20find%20themselves%20treated%20like%20second%20class%20citizens%20in%20the%20promised%20land.%20They%20became%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eolim%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20immigrants%2C%20pushed%20down%20the%20pecking%20order%20that%20favoured%20the%20Ashkenazi%20or%20European%20Jews.%20Those%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20North%20Africa%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Sephardi%20Jews%20%E2%80%93%20were%20considered%20culturally%20and%20socially%20inferior%20and%20were%20expected%20to%20integrate%20into%20a%20conception%20of%20Israel%20as%20an%20outpost%20of%20European%20enlightenment%20in%20a%20sea%20of%20primitive%20Arabic%20culture.%20The%20point%20is%20not%20just%20the%20material%20loss%20%E2%80%93%20though%20of%20course%20that%20was%20considerable.%20The%20more%20painful%20loss%20was%20that%20of%20history%2C%20of%20language%2C%20of%20self.%20In%20order%20for%20Israel%20to%20be%20a%20Jewish%20haven%20in%20hostile%20Arab%20neighbourhood%2C%20the%20links%20between%20Jews%20and%20Arabs%20had%20to%20be%20completely%20disavowed.%20The%20move%20to%20Israel%20erased%20a%20whole%20culture%20and%20history%20of%20being.%20Yusef%20was%20not%20able%20to%20reinvent%20himself%20and%20he%20died%20a%20silent%20shadow%20of%20his%20prosperous%2C%20generous%20self.%20Avi%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20a%20lament%20for%20people%20like%20his%20father%20who%20lost%20literally%20everything%20in%20the%20move%20to%20Zion%2C%20for%20whom%20Zion%20became%20the%20land%20of%20exile.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20this%20point%20of%20view%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMemoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20reckoning%20with%20a%20heritage%20and%20a%20past.%20In%20addition%20to%20acknowledging%20the%20injustice%20done%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enaqba%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20catastrophe%20of%201948%2C%20when%20over%20750%2C000%20Palestinians%20were%20forcibly%20displaced%20from%20the%20land%20of%20their%20ancestors%20(events%20that%20occur%20outside%20the%20purview%20of%20this%20memoir)%2C%20this%20book%20looks%20at%20the%20injustice%20done%20to%20Arab-Jews%20who%20were%20pushed%20out%20of%20the%20lands%20of%20their%20birth%20by%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20region.%20As%20with%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20who%20were%20denied%20the%20right%20of%20return%20by%20the%20new%20Jewish%20state%2C%20the%20injustice%20done%20to%20the%20Arab-Jews%20was%20then%20compounded%20by%20the%20devaluing%20and%20suppressing%20of%20their%20identities%20in%20Israel.%20They%20were%20brought%20in%20to%20Israel%20to%20fill%20the%20%E2%80%98empty%20spaces%E2%80%99%20created%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20Palestine%E2%80%99%2C%20even%20if%20they%20%E2%80%98had%20no%20desire%20whatsoever%20to%20relocate%20to%20Israel.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Then%2C%20to%20maintain%20the%20idea%20of%20Israel%20as%20an%20outpost%20of%20Jewish%20sanctuary%2C%20the%20links%20of%20the%20Arab-Jews%20to%20the%20land%20of%20their%20forefathers%20had%20to%20be%20denied%20and%20suppressed.%20The%20Jews%20of%20the%20Arab%20lands%20could%20have%20been%20a%20bridge%20to%20their%20Arab%20neighbours%20once%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20was%20established%20in%20Palestine.%20Instead%2C%20David%20Ben-Gurion%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%2C%20%E2%80%98built%20Israel%20as%20a%20fortress%20state%20with%20a%20siege%20mentality%20that%20attributed%20genocidal%20intentions%20to%20its%20neighbours.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20price%20for%20that%20decision%20is%20still%20being%20paid%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20third%20home%20in%20this%20memoir%20of%20%E2%80%98Three%20Worlds%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20that%20is%20London%2C%20which%20is%20where%20Avi%20Shlaim%20moved%20from%20Israel%20to%20complete%20his%20secondary%20education.%20He%20never%20moved%20back.%20Britain%20provided%20the%20foil%20for%20Israel%20in%20a%20way%2C%20because%20the%20social%20distinctions%20between%20Ashkenazi%20and%20Sephardi%20did%20not%20matter%20so%20much.%20He%20was%20now%20freer%20to%20shape%20his%20identity%20as%20he%20chose.%20Eventually%2C%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20distance%20allowed%20Avi%20to%20bring%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20objectivity%20to%20his%20study%20of%20Israel.%20This%20gradually%20resulted%20in%20his%20disillusionment%20with%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20as%20it%20is%20now%20and%20the%20Zionist%20project%20that%20deprived%20him%20of%20his%20homeland.%20As%20he%20explains%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20present%20impasse%20in%20Israel-Palestine%20resulted%2C%20at%20least%20partly%2C%20from%20the%20central%20assumption%20of%20Zionist%20discourse%2C%20namely%2C%20that%20Jews%20and%20Arabs%20are%20exclusive%20and%20antagonistic%20ethnic%20categories.%20The%20Zionist%20movement%20was%20in%20origin%20and%20in%20essence%20a%20European%20movement%20led%20by%20European%20Jews%20who%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20Jewish%20state%20for%20European%20Jews.%20It%20aspired%20to%20be%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20but%20not%20of%20the%20Middle%20East.%20It%20sought%20not%20the%20melding%20of%20cultures%20but%20the%20replacement%20of%20the%20local%20culture%20by%20a%20European%20one.%20By%20its%20very%20nature%2C%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20deepened%20the%20divisions%20between%20Israelis%20and%20Palestinians%2C%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20between%20Judaism%20and%20Islam%2C%20between%20Hebrew%20and%20Arabic.%20The%20Zionist%20movement%20and%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%20have%20actively%20worked%20to%20erase%20our%20common%20past%2C%20our%20intertwined%20histories%20and%20our%20centuries-old%20heritage%20of%20pluralism%2C%20religious%20tolerance%2C%20cosmopolitanism%20and%20co-existence.%20Above%20all%2C%20Zionism%20has%20discouraged%20us%20from%20seeing%20each%20other%20as%20fellow%20human%20beings.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20that%2C%20in%20essence%20is%20why%20this%20book%20is%20a%20must-read.%20Avi%20reminds%20us%20that%20beneath%20even%20the%20most%20intractable%20of%20conflicts%20are%20human%20beings%20%E2%80%93%20people%20with%20histories%2C%20cultures%20and%20stories.%20Once%20we%20allow%20ourselves%20to%20understand%20those%20histories%20and%20acknowledge%20the%20essential%20humanity%20of%20each%20other%2C%20we%20might%20start%20to%20find%20a%20way%20out%20of%20even%20the%20most%20impossibly%20antagonistic%20of%20relationships.%20It%20is%2C%20quite%20simply%2C%20an%20excellent%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPriyanjali%20Malik%20walked%20into%20her%20first%20tutorial%20with%20Avi%20Shlaim%20some%20twenty-five%20years%20ago.%20He%20guided%20her%20through%20her%20MPhil%2C%20provided%20advice%20on%20life%20and%20relationships%20and%20taught%20her%20how%20to%20become%20a%20scholar%20somewhere%20along%20the%20way.%20He%20even%20approved%20of%20the%20chap%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20marry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22tooltip%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703773177000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F15164743%2Ftaylor-brandon-Y8r0RTNrIWM-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-memoir-chronicles-how-israel-failed-to-become-the-promised-land-for-all-jews%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Avi%20Shlaim%E2%80%99s%20memoir%2C%20Three%20Worlds%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20an%20Arab-Jew%2C%20turns%20the%20spotlight%20back%20on%20some%20of%20the%20things%20that%20the%20Jewish%20nation%2C%20centred%20on%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20prefers%20to%20forget%20or%20suppress.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-memoir-chronicles-how-israel-failed-to-become-the-promised-land-for-all-jews%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russian%20poets%20get%20jail%20sentences%20for%20anti-war%20poetry%20reading%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703772869000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FCD92%2Fproduction%2F_132162625_artyom1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67833649%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Artyom%20Kamardin%20and%20Yegor%20Shtovba%20were%20detai