20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmnesty%20released%20its%20findings%20on%20December%2028%20as%20part%20of%20its%20partnership%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.is%2F2023.12.28-021126%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F12%2F27%2Findia-apple-iphone-hacking%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20wider%20investigation%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20Varadarajan%20has%20been%20targeted%20with%20the%20Israeli%20made%20spyware.%20As%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20in%202021%20as%20part%20of%20an%20investigation%20by%20a%20worldwide%20media%20consortium%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Pegasus%20Project%E2%80%99%2C%20his%20phone%20was%20among%20several%20other%20journalists%2C%20opposition%20politicians%20and%20human%20rights%20defenders%20on%20whose%20devices%20Amnesty%E2%80%99s%20Security%20Lab%20found%20Pegasus.%20The%20presence%20of%20the%20spyware%20on%20Magnale%E2%80%99s%20phone%20is%20especially%20concerning%20as%20the%20trigger%20for%20his%20selection%20as%20a%20target%20appears%20to%20be%20his%20investigation%20into%20the%20business%20affairs%20of%20the%20Adani%20group.%20As%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9COn%20Aug.%2023%2C%20the%20OCCRP%20emailed%20Adani%20seeking%20comment%20for%20a%20story%20it%20would%20publish%20a%20week%20later%20alleging%20that%20his%20brother%20was%20part%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3Eof%20a%20group%20that%20had%20secretly%20traded%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20the%20Adani%20Group%20conglomerate%E2%80%99s%20public%20stock%2C%20possibly%20in%20violation%20of%20Indian%20securities%20law.%20A%20forensic%20analysis%20of%20Mangnale%E2%80%99s%20phone%2C%20conducted%20by%20Amnesty%20International%20and%20shared%20with%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%2C%20found%20that%20within%2024%20hours%20of%20that%20inquiry%2C%20an%20attacker%20infiltrated%20the%20device%20and%20planted%C2%A0Pegasus%2C%20the%20notorious%20spyware%C2%A0that%20was%20developed%20by%20Israeli%20company%20NSO%20Group%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3Eand%20that%20NSO%20says%20is%20sold%20only%20to%20governments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20latest%20findings%20show%20that%20increasingly%2C%20journalists%20in%20India%20face%20the%20threat%20of%20unlawful%20surveillance%20simply%20for%20doing%20their%20jobs%2C%20alongside%20other%20tools%20of%20repression%20including%20imprisonment%20under%20draconian%20laws%2C%20smear%20campaigns%2C%20harassment%2C%20and%20intimidation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Donncha%20%C3%93%20Cearbhaill%2C%20head%20of%20Amnesty%20International%E2%80%99s%20Security%20Lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmnesty%20said%20its%20Security%20Lab%20%E2%80%9Cfirst%20observed%20indications%20of%20renewed%20Pegasus%20spyware%20threats%20towards%20individuals%20in%20India%20during%20a%20regular%20technical%20monitoring%20exercise%20in%20June%202023%2C%20a%20number%20of%20months%20after%20media%20reported%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20was%20seeking%20to%20procure%20a%20new%20commercial%20spyware%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Apple%20issued%20threat%20notifications%20globally%20to%20iPhone%20users%20who%20may%20have%20been%20targeted%20by%20%E2%80%9Cstate-sponsored%20attackers%E2%80%9D%2C%20Varadarajan%2C%20Mangnale%20and%20a%20number%20of%20other%20journalists%20and%20opposition%20politicians%20in%20India%20received%20the%20notifications.%20Among%20those%20who%20went%20public%20at%20the%20time%20were%20Mahua%20Moitra%20of%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20a%20prominent%20critic%20of%20the%20Adani%20group%2C%20and%20Ravi%20Nair%2C%20a%20journalist%20with%20OCCRP%20who%20was%20working%20on%20an%20Adani%20story%20with%20Mangnale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Amnesty%20International%E2%80%99s%20Security%20Lab%20undertook%20a%20forensic%20analysis%20on%20the%20phones%20of%20Varadarajan%20and%20Mangnale%2C%20the%20press%20release%20said%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9Cfound%20traces%20of%20Pegasus%20spyware%20activity%20on%20devices%20owned%20by%20both%20Indian%20journalists%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Security%20Lab%20recovered%20evidence%20from%20Anand%20Mangnale%E2%80%99s%20device%20of%20a%20zero-click%20exploit%20which%20was%20sent%20to%20his%20phone%20over%20iMessage%20on%2023%20August%202023%2C%20and%20designed%20to%20covertly%20install%20the%20Pegasus%20spyware.%20The%20phone%20was%20running%20iOS%2016.6%2C%20the%20latest%20version%20available%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CA%20zero-click%20exploit%20refers%20to%20malicious%20software%20that%20enables%20spyware%20to%20be%20installed%20on%20a%20device%20without%20requiring%20any%20user%20action%20from%20the%20target%2C%20such%20as%20clicking%20on%20a%20link.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Security%20Lab%20also%20identified%20an%20attacker-controlled%20email%20address%20used%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Pegasus%20attack%20on%20his%20device.%20The%20recovered%20samples%20are%20consistent%20with%20the%20NSO%20Group%E2%80%99s%20BLASTPASS%20exploit%2C%20publicly%20identified%20by%20Citizen%20Lab%20in%20September%202023%20and%20patched%20by%20Apple%20in%20iOS%2016.6.1%20(CVE-2023-41064).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAnand%20Mangnale%E2%80%99s%20phone%20was%20vulnerable%20to%20this%20zero-click%20exploit%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20attack.%20It%20is%20currently%20unclear%20if%20the%20exploit%20attempt%20resulted%20in%20a%20successful%20compromise%20of%20his%20device.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Varadarajan%E2%80%99s%20phone%2C%20Amnesty%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsecuritylab.amnesty.org%2Flatest%2F2023%2F12%2Fpegasus-zero-click-exploit-threatens-journalists-in-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforensic%20report%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Security%20Lab%20reviewed%20forensic%20records%20from%20Siddharth%20Varadarajan%E2%80%99s%20iPhone%2011%20and%20identified%20traces%20which%20confirms%20that%20his%20phone%20was%20also%20target%20with%20NSO%20Group%E2%80%99s%20Pegasus%20spyware%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CHomeKit%20logs%20from%20Siddharth%20Varadarajan%20iPhone%20show%20that%20the%20was%20also%20targeted%20by%20the%20same%20Pegasus%20attacker%20email%20account%20used%20to%20target%20Anand%20Mangnale.%20The%20recovered%20HomeKit%20logs%20show%20that%20the%20%3Cstrong%3Enatalymarinova%40proton.me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Apple%20account%20interacted%20with%20his%20device%E2%80%99s%20HomeKit%20service%20on%2016%20October%202023%20around%2014%3A36%3A09%20UTC.%20At%20the%20time%20his%20phone%20was%20running%20iOS%20version%2016.6.1%20which%20was%20not%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20BLASTPAST%20attack.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20iVerify%2C%20a%20New%20York%20security%20firm%20it%20engaged%20to%20test%20the%20phones%20of%20some%20of%20the%20Indian%20politicians%20on%20the%20list%20of%20those%20who%20received%20a%20spyware%20alert%20from%20Apple%2C%20found%20tell-tale%20footprints%20of%20targetting%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIVerify%20examined%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20phone%20backup%20and%20confirmed%20that%20she%20had%20received%20an%20Apple%20warning.%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20also%20saw%20urgent%20crash%20reports%20that%2C%20together%20with%20other%20digital%20records%2C%20suggested%20the%20device%20had%20been%20hacked.%20The%20company%20also%20found%20a%20threat%20notification%20and%20suspicious%20activity%20on%20the%20phone%20of%20Praveen%20Chakravarty%2C%20head%20of%20the%20opposition%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20data%20analytics%20department.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20renewed%20evidence%20of%20Pegasus%20being%20used%20against%20journalists%20in%20India%20comes%20more%20than%20a%20year%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20technical%20committee%20it%20had%20appointed%20to%20probe%20allegations%20of%20illegal%20surveillance%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-pegasus-technical-committee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20evidence%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmalware%E2%80%99%20in%20as%20many%20as%20five%20mobile%20phones%20which%20it%20tested%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20then%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%2C%20N.V.%20Ramana%2C%20had%20also%20said%20that%20that%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20had%20refused%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20committee%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20being%20asked%20by%20the%20court%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20technical%20committee%20was%20created%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20confirm%20or%20deny%20its%20purchase%20and%20use%20of%20Pegasus%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20not%20held%20the%20government%20in%20contempt%20and%20has%20also%20not%20taken%20any%20further%20action%20on%20the%20findings%20it%20has.%20The%20committee%E2%80%99s%20report%20itself%20was%20not%20made%20public%2C%20citing%20privacy%20concerns%2C%20though%20some%20of%20the%20journalists%20who%20had%20submitted%20their%20devices%20for%20testing%20had%20said%20they%20had%20no%20objection%20to%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20report%20being%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPressure%20on%20Apple%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%3Cem%3E%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20story%20also%20documents%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20control%20the%20narrative%20soon%20after%20Apple%E2%80%99s%20October%20notiications%20were%20issued%2C%20which%20included%20putting%20pressure%20on%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20executives%20in%20India%20to%20themselves%20downplay%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20warning%20they%20had%20just%20issued%20to%20iPhone%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-qa%3D%5C%22article-body%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSenior%20Modi%20administration%20officials%20called%20Apple%20India%E2%80%99s%20managing%20director%2C%20Virat%20Bhatia%2C%20after%20the%20news%20broke%2C%20said%20two%20people%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter.%20One%20of%20the%20people%20said%20Indian%20officials%20asked%20Apple%20to%20withdraw%20the%20warnings%20and%20say%20it%20had%20made%20a%20mistake.%20After%20a%20heated%20discussion%2C%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20India%20office%20said%20the%20most%20it%20could%20do%20was%20put%20out%20a%20public%20statement%20that%20emphasized%20certain%20caveats%20that%20Apple%20had%20already%20listed%20on%20its%20tech%20support%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.is%2Fo%2FtjMEN%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fen-in%2F102174%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epage%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eabout%20the%20warnings.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703763294000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F02143130%2Fpegasus397131.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpegasus-used-to-target-the-wires-founding-editor-reporter-working-on-adani-amnesty-confirms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20OCCRP%20sent%20queries%20to%20the%20Adani%20group%20on%20August%2024%20and%20%26quot%3Bwithin%2024%20hours%20of%20that%20inquiry%2C%20an%20attacker%20infiltrated%20the%20device%20and%20planted%C2%A0Pegasus%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20phone%20of%20its%20reporter%2C%20Anand%20Mangnale%2C%20the%20Washington%20Post%20and%20Amnesty%20International%20have%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpegasus-used-to-target-the-wires-founding-editor-reporter-working-on-adani-amnesty-confirms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Qatar%20Court%20Commutes%20Indian%20Navy%20Veterans'%20Death%20Sentence%20to%20Prison%20Terms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24160310%2FCourt-of-appeals.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Two%20months%20after%20sentencing%20eight%20Indian%20Navy%20veterans%20to%20death%2C%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20reduced%20their%20capital%20punishment%20to%20imprisonment%20of%20varying%20terms%20on%20Thursday%20(December%2028).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20noted%20the%20%E2%80%9Cverdict%20today%20of%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20of%20Qatar%20in%20the%20Dahra%20Global%20case%2C%20in%20which%20the%20sentences%20have%20been%20reduced%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%20said%20that%20Vipul%2C%20the%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20Qatar%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20veterans%E2%80%99%20family%20members%20were%20present%20in%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20when%20the%20order%20was%20delivered.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20that%20a%20detailed%20judgement%20is%20awaited%2C%20the%20MEA%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cin%20close%20touch%20with%20the%20legal%20team%20as%20well%20as%20the%20family%20members%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20next%20steps%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20usual%2C%20the%20ministry%20explained%20that%20it%20would%20not%20make%20any%20further%20comments%20at%20this%20juncture%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20to%20the%20confidential%20and%20sensitive%20nature%20of%20proceedings%20of%20this%20case%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20stood%20by%20them%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20matter%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20extend%20all%20consular%20and%20legal%20assistance.%20We%20will%20also%20continue%20to%20take%20up%20the%20matter%20with%20the%20Qatari%20authorities%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20the%20veterans%E2%80%99%20sentences%20were%20reduced%2C%20but%20it%20is%20understood%20that%20they%20have%20been%20given%20varying%20prison%20terms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20eight%20men%20are%20Captain%20Navtej%20Singh%20Gill%2C%20Captain%20Birendra%20Kumar%20Verma%2C%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Vasisht%2C%20Commodore%20Amit%20Nagpal%2C%20Commodore%20Purnendu%20Tiwari%2C%20Commodore%20Sugunakar%20Pakala%2C%20Commodore%20Sanjeev%20Gupta%20and%20Sailor%20Ragesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fqatar-eight-former-indian-navy-officers-handed-death-penalty%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20October%2026%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20Court%20of%20First%20Instance%20handed%20the%20death%20penalty%20to%20the%20veterans%2C%20who%20had%20been%20detained%20for%20over%20a%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmployed%20by%20the%20now-defunct%20Omani%20private%20firm%20Dahra%20Global%20Technologies%20and%20Consultancy%20Services%2C%20they%20were%20contracted%20for%20providing%20training%20and%20related%20services%20to%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20armed%20forces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20charges%20have%20never%20been%20made%20public%2C%20media%20reports%20hinted%20at%20the%20possibility%20of%20their%20being%20charged%20with%20espionage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20shocked%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20October%20verdict%2C%20but%20had%20even%20then%20refrained%20from%20making%20further%20comments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbout%20four%20weeks%20later%2C%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fqatar-court-accepts-appeal-application-against-death-sentence-to-8-indian-navy-veterans%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccepted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20deliberations%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20against%20the%20veterans%E2%80%99%20death%20sentence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20Congress%20party%20expressed%20relief%20with%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeals%E2%80%99%20decision%20in%20Qatar%20to%20reduce%20the%20death%20penalty%20for%20eight%20Indian%20Navy%20veterans.%20The%20party%20expressed%20hope%20that%20not%20only%20will%20their%20jail%20sentences%20be%20overturned%20but%20also%20that%20they%20will%20be%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20shares%20its%20immediate%20relief%20along%20with%20the%20entire%20nation%20that%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20in%20Qatar%20has%20decided%20not%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20the%20death%20penalty%20on%208%20former%20Indian%20Navy%20officers.%20While%20fuller%20details%20are%20awaited%20we%20express%20the%20hope%20that%20even%20the%20jail%20sentence%20that%20has%20replaced%20the%20death%20penalty%20will%20be%20set%20aside%20and%20the%20officers%20will%20be%20set%20free%2C%E2%80%9D%20Congress%20General%20Secretary%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1740338336416301250%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20commutation%20of%20their%20death%20sentences%2C%20the%20eight%20Indians%20become%20eligible%20for%20repatriation%20to%20India%20under%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmindia.gov.in%2Fen%2Fnews_updates%2Flist-of-agreements-mous-exchanged-by-external-affairs-minister-and-her-qatari-counterpart-dr-khalid-bin-mohammed-al-attiyah-during-the-visit-of-emir-of-qatar-to-india%2F%5C%22%20data-stringif