%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FHistory-Ancient-Egypt-John-Romer%2Fdp%2F0141399716%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1%3Fqid%3D1703586588%26s%3Dbooks%26sr%3D1-1%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FHistory-Ancient-Egypt-John-Romer%2Fdp%2F0141399716%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1%3Fqid%3D1703586588%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks%26amp%3Bsr%3D1-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Efirst%20volume%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20tracing%20from%20prehistory%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20first%20pyramids%2C%20that%20stands%20out%20for%20its%20meticulous%20weaving%20of%20archaeological%20research%20and%20story-telling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Jahnavi%20Sen%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Education%20of%20Yuri%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Jerry%20Pinto%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20may%20have%20thought%20I%E2%80%99d%20had%20my%20fill%20of%20coming-of-age%20stories%2C%20but%20Pinto%E2%80%99s%20telling%20of%20a%20young%20Yuri%E2%80%99s%20journey%20through%20boyhood%20and%20beyond%2C%20dealing%20with%20embarrassment%2C%20loneliness%2C%20loss%2C%20grief%2C%20love%20and%20sexuality%20is%20a%20path%20I%E2%80%99m%20so%20glad%20I%20went%20down.%20It%20felt%20both%20like%20a%20warm%20hug%20and%20a%20gentle%20nudge%20to%20not%20ignore%20the%20realities%20and%20feelings%20that%20may%20sit%20a%20little%20uncomfortable%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Yuri%E2%80%99s%20beautiful%2C%20longstanding%2C%20passionate%20relationship%20with%20books%20only%20made%20it%20that%20much%20more%20exciting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Ajoy%20Ashirwad%20Mahaprashasta%3A%20%3Cem%3ELeft%20Is%20Not%20Woke%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Susan%20Neiman%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeiman%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20an%20impassioned%20defence%20of%20universalism%20and%20belief%20in%20moral%20progress%20in%20an%20age%20where%20politics%20is%20increasingly%20being%20understood%20as%20inherently%20a%20transactional%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20its%20people%2C%20and%20nothing%20more.%20The%20rise%20of%20right%20wing%2C%20populist%20regimes%20across%20the%20world%20in%20the%20last%20few%20decades%20has%20also%20coincided%20with%20a%20marked%20growth%20of%20pretentious%20vanity%20projects%20that%20are%20often%20passed%20off%20as%20Leftist%20politics.%20Neiman%E2%80%99s%20book%20canonises%20a%20solid%20Leftist%20critique%20of%20market-determined%20%E2%80%9Cwokeism%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20being%20equally%20careful%20to%20distinguish%20itself%20from%20the%20right-wing%E2%80%99s%20tired%20demonisation%20of%20all%20democratic%20voices.%20Neiman%20explores%20how%20%E2%80%9Cwokeism%E2%80%9D%2C%20although%20driven%20by%20the%20desire%20to%20defend%20the%20underdog%2C%20invariably%20descends%20into%20an%20abyss%20that%20is%20quite%20similar%20to%20the%20defeatist%2C%20cynical%20world%20view%20of%20the%20global%20Right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Soumashree%20Sarkar%3A%20%3Cem%3ENights%20Of%20Plague%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Orhan%20Pamuk%20(translated%20by%20Ekin%20Oklap)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurkish%20author%20Orhan%20Pamuk%E2%80%99s%20novel%2C%20set%20in%20a%20fictitious%20island%20on%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%2C%20is%20on%20%E2%80%93%20of%20all%20things%20%E2%80%93%20the%20plague%20of%20the%20last%20century.%20Incredibly%2C%20Pamuk%20began%20working%20on%20the%20book%20much%20before%20our%20own%20version%20of%20the%20plague%20set%20in.%20So%20as%20realtime%20events%20took%20place%20surrounding%20COVID-19%2C%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20missives%20against%20divisions%20deepening%20during%20disease%20and%20on%20how%20ignoring%20it%20always%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20better%20option%20than%20tackling%20it%20rang%20cruelly%20true.%20Pamuk%E2%80%99s%20language%2C%20read%20in%20translation%2C%20is%20languorous%20and%20the%20book%20is%20irreverent%20enough%20to%20lull%20you%20into%20a%20sense%20of%20comfort%20with%20its%20grim%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Seema%20Chishti%3A%20%3Cem%3ETurning%20Over%20the%20Pebbles%3A%20A%20Life%20in%20Cricket%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20in%20the%20Mind%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Mike%20Brearley%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMike%20Brearley%E2%80%99s%20memoirs%20were%20a%20superb%20and%20moving%20read.%20There%20is%20so%20much%20to%20learn%20from%20this%20fine%20cricketer%2C%20philosopher%2C%20psychoanalyst%20and%20team%20captain.%20He%20is%20honest%2C%20his%20book%20makes%20you%20work%20hard%20to%20learn%20and%20grasp%20concepts%20which%20he%20does%20not%20hesitate%20to%20throw%20at%20a%20reader.%20There%20is%20a%20reason%20he%20is%20telling%20it%20all%20%E2%80%93%20read%20it%20till%20the%20end%20to%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Meenakshi%20Tiwari%3A%20%3Cem%3ERadio%20for%20the%20Millions%3A%20Hindi-Urdu%20Broadcasting%20Across%20Borders%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20Isabel%20Huacuja%20Alonso%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENon-fiction%20is%20rarely%20considered%20%E2%80%98interesting%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20ways%20fiction%20is%2C%20but%20if%20I%20have%20to%20chose%20one%20book%20that%20I%20found%20interesting%20in%202023%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20this%20one.%20Alonso%20is%20a%20historian%20of%20South%20Asia%20and%20assistant%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20University.%20It%20started%20as%20a%20professional%20assignment%20as%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20interview%20her%2C%20but%20her%20research%20surprised%20me.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20the%20history%20of%20the%20radio%2C%20but%20about%20three%20regions%20and%20how%20radio%20waves%20have%20been%20used%20as%20a%20political%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20little%20more%20than%20200%20pages%2C%20she%20depicts%20how%20Indians%20were%20introduced%20to%20the%20world%20of%20radio%2C%20how%20Subhas%20Chandra%20Bose%20promoted%20radio%20as%20a%20form%20of%20defiance%20against%20British%20rule%2C%20how%20post%20independence%20the%20Indian%20government%20tried%20to%20turn%20radio%20%E2%80%98nationalist%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20ever-loved%20Radio%20Ceylon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20chapter%20on%20All%20India%20Radio%E2%80%99s%20Urdu%20service%20and%20its%20listenership%20in%20Pakistan.%20At%20one%20point%20it%20records%20how%20the%20radio%20became%20a%20bridge%20between%20two%20nations%2C%20as%20listeners%20from%20the%20other%20side%20used%20to%20write%20letters%20to%20the%20broadcasters%20to%20ask%20about%20places%20in%20India%20were%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%20The%20book%20shares%20pieces%20of%20common%20people%E2%80%99s%20history%20and%20the%20many%20ways%20Partition%20affected%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20well-researched%20book%20explains%20how%20listening%20is%20an%20integral%20component%20of%20history.%20As%20a%20person%20who%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20and%20interested%20in%20radio%20as%20a%20medium%2C%20this%20book%20has%20given%20new%20dimensions%20to%20my%20perspective%20on%20audio%20broadcasting%20and%20the%20power%20of%20soundwaves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E10.%20Faiyaz%20Ahmad%20Wajeeh%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bride%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Hari%20Mohan%20Jha%2C%20translated%20by%20Lalit%20Kumar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Bride%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20English%20translation%20of%20Hari%20Mohan%20Jha%E2%80%99s%20novel%20%3Cem%3EKanyadan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1930)%20which%20is%20considered%20a%20classic%20in%20Maithili%20literature%2C%20is%20a%20real%20page-turner.%20While%20reading%20the%20novel%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20going%20into%20deep%20nostalgia.%20I%20felt%20as%20if%20I%20was%20having%20a%20serious%20dialogue%20with%20the%20unusual%20but%20relevant%20writing%2C%20the%20ethos%20of%20which%20I%20have%20personally%20witnessed%20and%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20effectively%20addresses%20issues%20like%20dowry%20and%20child%20marriage%2C%20emphasising%20the%20illiteracy%20of%20girls%20and%20their%20mismatched%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20a%2013-year-old%20illiterate%20girl%2C%20Buchiya%2C%20and%20English%20graduate%20C.C.%20Mishra%2C%20is%20the%20saga%20of%20how%20a%20girl%20or%20woman%20can%20exist%20in%20two%20contradictory%20worlds.%20The%20narration%20of%20the%20story%20also%20brings%20in%20fascinating%20tales%20of%20Mithila%E2%80%99s%20customs%20and%20traditions%2C%20including%20its%20folk%20songs%20and%20various%20superstitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20is%20extraordinarily%20striking%20because%20the%20novelist%20hardly%20leaves%20an%20opportunity%20to%20criticise%20an%20issue%20%E2%80%93whether%20small%20or%20big.%20He%20has%20brilliantly%20taken%20on%20the%20caste%20system%20while%20putting%20forth%20uncomfortable%20questions.%20He%20has%20also%20questioned%20patriarchy%20while%20highlighting%20the%20menace%20of%20illiteracy%20among%20girls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novelist%20must%20be%20applauded%20for%20narrating%20the%20conflict%20between%20India%20and%20British%20India%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20University%20teacher%20Lalit%20Kumar%20has%20successfully%20adopted%20this%20classic%20into%20English%2C%20finding%20the%20perfect%20vocabularies.%20I%20consider%20this%20translation%20a%20significant%20accomplishment%20as%20there%20has%20been%20no%20English%20translation%20of%20a%20classic%20Maithili%20novel%20before%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20this%2C%20I%20thoroughly%20enjoyed%20Mohan%20Mukta%E2%80%99s%20collection%20of%20poems%2C%20%3Cem%3EHimalaya%20Dalit%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20is%20breaking%20the%20norms%20of%20poetry%20to%20try%20and%20establish%20a%20deep%20cultural%20resistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E11.%20Aquilur%20Rahman%3A%20%3Cem%3EPoetry%20of%20The%20First%20World%20War%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20selected%20by%20Edward%20Hudson%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20of%20those%20days%20when%20I%20went%20searching%20for%20solace%20in%20the%20smells%20of%20yellowed%20pages%20in%20old%20book%20stores%2C%20I%20scrambled%20through%20piles%20and%20under%20one%20corner%2C%20beneath%20a%20hundred%20others%2C%20I%20found%20my%20book%20of%20the%20year%3A%20%3Cem%3EPoetry%20of%20The%20First%20World%20War%3C%2Fem%3E%20selected%20by%20Edward%20Hudson%2C%20with%20a%20preface%20by%20Jon%20Stallworthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20year%20is%20ending%2C%20with%20wars%20still%20around%20us%2C%20Sir%20Henry%20Newbolt%20(1924)%20was%20right%3A%20%E2%80%98I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20these%20shell-shocked%20war%20poems%20will%20move%20our%20grandchildren%20greatly.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t.%20Yet%2C%20I%20take%20the%20one%20that%20got%20me%20off%20my%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Here%20Dead%20Lie%20We%E2%80%99%20by%20A.E.%20Housman%2C%20published%20in%201917%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20dead%20lie%20we%20because%20we%20did%20not%20choose%3Cbr%3E%5CnTo%20live%20and%20shame%20the%20land%20from%20which%20we%20sprung.%3Cbr%3E%5CnLife%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20is%20nothing%20much%20to%20lose%3B%3Cbr%3E%5CnBut%20young%20men%20think%20it%20is%2C%20and%20we%20were%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E12.%20Sangeeta%20Barooah%20Pisharoty%3A%20%3Cem%3EFear%20of%20Flying%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20Erica%20Jong%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20so%20many%20books%20and%20so%20little%20time!%202023%20shall%20go%20down%20in%20my%20trajectory%20as%20the%20year%20when%20I%20tried%20catching%20up%20with%20some%20controversial%20titles%20that%20I%20never%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20pick%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20book%20that%20I%20finished%20reading%20this%20year%20is%20the%20Penguin%20classic%2C%20the%20provocative%20%3Cem%3EFear%20of%20Flying%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20indomitable%20Erica%20Jong.%20The%20copy%20I%20picked%20up%20was%20the%2040th%20anniversary%20edition%20with%20a%20foreword%20by%20the%20American%20playwright%20and%20writer%20Theresa%20Rebeck.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20reason%20I%20went%20for%20the%20book%20was%20also%20because%20it%20was%20penned%20in%201973%2C%20the%20year%20of%20my%20birth.%20In%20India%2C%20a%20woman%20talking%20candidly%20about%20female%20sexuality%20and%20desire%20was%20a%20taboo%20then%3B%20it%20is%20taboo%20still.%20Things%20may%20have%20changed%20now%20in%20the%20West%20but%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20it%20was%20definitely%20an%20eyebrow%20raiser.%20Jong%2C%20through%20the%20life%20of%20a%20young%20poetess%2C%20explored%20womanhood%20with%20a%20never-before-seen%20honesty%20that%20went%20on%20to%20also%20define%20self-expression%20during%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20feminism%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2013%2F12%2F19%2Ffashion%2FFear-of-Flying-Erica-Jong.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20celebrating%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%2040th%20anniversary%20recalled%20John%20Updike%20equating%20the%20book%20with%20%3Cem%3EA%20Catcher%20in%20the%20Rye%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20quoted%20Henry%20Miller%20predicting%20that%20it%20would%20%E2%80%9Cmake%20literary%20history%E2%80%9D%20for%20its%20%E2%80%9Cwisdom%20about%20the%20eternal%20man-woman%20problem%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJong%E2%80%99s%20book%20also%20contributed%20to%20the%20English%20language%20two%20controversial%20expressions.%20One%20was%20%E2%80%98zipless%E2%80%99.%20The%20%3Cem%3ENYT%3C%2Fem%3E%20write-up%20had%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20second%20of%20which%20cannot%20be%20printed%2C%20even%20today%2C%20in%20this%20newspaper.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E13.%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3A%20%3Cem%3ERumi%E2%80%99s%20Secret%3A%20The%20Life%20of%20the%20Sufi%20Poet%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20Love%20by%20Brad%20Gooch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20entire%20life%20has%20come%20down%20to%20three%20words%20%E2%80%93%20I%20was%20raw%2C%20I%20was%20cooked%2C%20I%20was%20burned.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20this%20year%20I%20finished%20reading%20this%20book%2C%20and%20it%20has%20kept%20me%20hooked%20throughout%20the%20year.%20It%20talks%20meticulously%20about%20many%20unknown%20and%20also%20misrepresented%20aspects%20of%20Rumi%E2%80%99s%20life%20and%20work.%20It%20explores%20deep%20to%20l