e-370-supreme-court-bbc-media%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%20four%20disturbing%20developments%20of%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20so%20while%20delivering%20the%20Smt.%20Bansari%20Sheth%20Endowment%20Lecture%20on%20%E2%80%98Constitution%3A%20Checks%20and%20Balances%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20he%20cited%20three%20other%20worrisome%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20were%20the%20constitutionally%20flawed%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20upholding%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20the%20Modi%20regime%E2%80%99s%20raid%20on%20the%20BBC%20for%20a%20documentary%20on%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%2C%20and%20the%20passage%20of%20a%20Bill%20in%20parliament%20concerning%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20election%20commissioner(s)%20by%20a%20committee%20in%20which%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20government%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala%20governor%20took%20the%20decision%20on%20those%20Bills%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fthiruvananthapuram%2Fkerala-governor-oks-1-bill-reserves-7-for-president-nod%2Farticleshow%2F105572896.cms%5C%22%3Ea%20day%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20to%20take%20up%20the%20Kerala%20government%E2%80%99s%20petition%20accusing%20the%20governor%20of%20%E2%80%9Csubverting%E2%80%9D%20the%20constitution%20and%20acting%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9Carbitrary%E2%80%9D%20manner%20by%20keeping%20the%20Bills%20pending%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cindefinite%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20paralysing%20the%20legislative%20functioning%20of%20the%20elected%20assembly%20and%20subverting%20its%20law-making%20process.%20His%20action%20was%20not%20in%20tune%20with%20his%20mandate%20in%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20provides%20that%20a%20governor%20should%20take%20a%20decision%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20on%20Bills%20sent%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20impeding%20the%20legislative%20functioning%20of%20an%20assembly%2C%20the%20governor%2C%20who%20takes%20the%20oath%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpreserve%2C%20protect%20and%20defend%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D%20is%20flagrantly%20violating%20it%20in%20letter%20and%20spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-as-ruling-partys-storm-troopers%5C%22%3EGovernors%20as%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Storm%20Troopers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernors%20sitting%20on%20Bills%20stifle%20law-making%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20rather%20extraordinary%20that%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fparliament-proceedings-three-more-opposition-mps-suspended-as-protest-over-mass-suspension-continues%2Farticle67661514.ece%5C%22%3E146%20MPs%20from%20the%20opposition%20parties%20have%20been%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20both%20Houses%20of%20parliament%2C%20governments%20formed%20by%20opposition%20parties%20in%20several%20states%20are%20being%20checkmated%20by%20governors%20who%2C%20as%20appointees%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20are%20stifling%20their%20legislative%20apparatus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnelected%20governors%20have%20no%20authority%20to%20impede%20the%20functioning%20of%20elected%20legislatures.%20When%20a%20governor%20refers%20a%20Bill%20to%20the%20president%2C%20the%20Bill%20is%20actually%20referred%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India.%20Those%20Bills%20are%20not%20directly%20sent%20to%20the%20president%20by%20the%20governor.%20They%20are%20sent%20to%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%2C%20which%20examines%20them%20after%20getting%20advice%20from%20concerned%20ministries%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India%2C%20and%20submits%20them%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20those%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20legislature%20and%20embodying%20the%20legislative%20intent%20of%20that%20assembly%20get%20subordinated%20to%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20the%20president%2C%20acting%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20government%2C%20does%20not%20give%20her%2Fhis%20assent%2C%20then%20those%20Bills%20are%20dead.%20It%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20the%20seven%20Bills%20from%20Kerala%20would%20meet%20such%20a%20fate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecommendations%20of%20the%20Sarkaria%20Commission%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarkaria%20Commission%20report%20on%20Centre-state%20relations%2C%20and%20its%20observations%20and%20recommendations%20contained%20in%20a%20separate%20chapter%20titled%20%E2%80%9CReservation%20of%20Bills%20by%20Governors%20for%20President%E2%80%99s%20Consideration%20and%20Promulgation%20of%20Ordinances%E2%80%9D%2C%20are%20of%20great%20relevance%20in%20this%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20invoked%20the%20study%20team%20of%20the%20administrative%20reforms%20commission%2C%20which%20had%20noted%20that%20the%20reservation%20of%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Bills%20by%20governors%20for%20presidential%20consideration%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Ccontrary%20to%20the%20federal%20spirit%20of%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Farif-mohammed-khan-pinarayi-vijayan-kerala%5C%22%3EIn%20Arif%20Mohammed%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20Steadfast%20Opposition%20to%20Kerala%20Govt%2C%20a%20Hint%20of%20His%20Usual%20Politics%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commission%20observed%20that%20such%20powers%20%E2%80%9Care%20intended%20to%20subserve%20the%20broad%20purpose%20of%20cooperative%20federalism%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20Union-state%20legislative%20relations%E2%80%9D%20and%20when%20%E2%80%9Cused%20sparingly%20in%20proper%20cases%2C%20e.g.%20where%20the%20Bill%20relates%20to%20a%20matter%20falling%20clearly%20within%20the%20Union%20List%2C%20it%20serves%20a%20useful%20purpose%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20then%20quoted%20constitutional%20expert%20D.D.%20Basu%2C%20who%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20powers%20of%20governors%20to%20refer%20Bills%20to%20the%20president%2C%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6its%20use%20cannot%20be%20extended%20to%20such%20an%20extent%20as%20to%20install%20the%20Union%20executive%20over%20the%20head%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20legislature%20in%20matters%20legislative.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commission%20recommended%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cneedless%20reservation%20of%20Bills%20for%20%5Bthe%5D%20president%E2%80%99s%20consideration%20should%20be%20avoided%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%20instructive%20to%20note%20that%20it%20recommended%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20matter%20of%20salutary%20convention%2C%20a%20reference%20should%20be%20disposed%20of%20by%20the%20president%20within%20a%20period%20of%20four%20months%20from%20the%20date%20on%20which%20the%20reference%20is%20received%20by%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20example%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20was%20prime%20minister%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20requested%20him%20to%20expeditiously%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20three%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20assembly%20and%20referred%20to%20the%20president%20by%20the%20governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20gave%20his%20assent%20in%20three%20months.%20It%20demonstrated%20how%2C%20through%20deliberation%20and%20consultation%2C%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20governance%20could%20be%20adopted%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20example%20and%20those%20utterances%20of%20the%20Commission%20assume%20greater%20significance%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitutional%20role%20of%20governors%20and%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20chapter%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98Role%20of%20Governors%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20Sarkaria%20Commission%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20part%20which%20the%20governor%20plays%20to%20help%20maintain%20the%20democratic%20form%20of%20government%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20constitution%20is%20of%20vital%20importance%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20ultimate%20analysis%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20observance%20of%20the%20constitutional%20provisions%20is%20the%20soundest%20guarantee%20of%20enduring%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20governors%20in%20most%20opposition-run%20states%20act%20in%20impeding%20the%20legislative%20functioning%20of%20elected%20assemblies%20raises%20questions%20about%20their%20actions%20to%20safeguard%20our%20unity%20and%20integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fs-n-sahu%5C%22%3ES.N.%20Sahu%3C%2Fa%3E%20served%20as%20officer%20on%20special%20duty%20to%20President%20K.R.%20Narayan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703749585000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03132819%2FF7m7Y5YaIAAeDNr.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkerala-governor-withholding-assent-bills%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Sarkaria%20Commission%20report%20on%20Centre-state%20relations%20observed%20that%20a%20governor's%20power%20to%20reserve%20Bills%20for%20presidential%20consideration%20must%20be%20%E2%80%9Cused%20sparingly%E2%80%9D%20and%20in%20limited%20contexts%2C%20adding%20that%20reserving%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Bills%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20the%20constitution's%20federal%20spirit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkerala-governor-withholding-assent-bills%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Intention%20Is%20to%20Have%20a%20Saffronised%20Pakistan%E2%80%99%3A%20Former%20Top%20Cop%20on